INSERT INTO `recipe` VALUES (1,'spinach with eggs',0,'greek',2,'This is a greek-inspired breakfast dish that I was first introduced to as a child while staying at a hotel during one of our many family holidays to Cyprus. My version of the recipe predominantly comprises slowly cooked onions, tomatoes, spinach and eggs, topped with an indulgent drizzling of melted butter and spices. A simple slice of fresh bread, and a small handful of olives on the side ensure a deliciously hearty start to the day, and all in under 30 minutes.',5,'egg','spinach with eggs','homemade favorites',2,'Use fresh spinach for the best flavor and texture.','Season the eggs with your favorite herbs or spices for added flavor.','Serve with a slice of crusty bread or toast for a complete meal.',15,15,'https://img.jamieoliver.com/jamieoliver/recipe-database/156460151.jpg?tr=w-800,h-1066'),(2,'creme caramele',1,'french',3,'Sometimes nothing beats an old-school classic like the crème caramel. Serving up this popular dessert with magical passion fruit gives it a fresh and fruity twist to really cut through the indulgence.',6,'egg','creme caramele','sweet indulgences',6,'Be patient when making the caramel, and avoid stirring it to prevent crystallization.','Use room temperature ingredients for the custard to ensure smooth texture.','Allow the creme caramel to cool completely before unmolding for best results.',30,30,'https://img.jamieoliver.com/jamieoliver/recipe-database/155517325.jpg?tr=w-800,h-1066'),(3,'italian baked eggs',0,'italian',2,'Italian baked eggs, a delectable dish hailing from the heart of Italy, offer a tantalizing blend of flavors and textures. This savory masterpiece combines the richness of eggs with vibrant Italian ingredients, typically including tomatoes, garlic, herbs, and cheeses like mozzarella or Parmesan. The eggs are gently baked to perfection, allowing their yolks to remain delightfully runny while the surrounding ingredients meld together, creating a harmonious symphony of taste. Whether served as a hearty breakfast, a satisfying brunch, or a comforting dinner, Italian baked eggs promise to transport your taste buds to the sunny shores of Italy with each indulgent bite. Buon appetito!',6,'egg',NULL,'classic comfort',2,'Customize with your favorite Italian herbs and spices for added flavor.','Add a sprinkle of cheese on top before baking for a delicious golden crust.','Serve with crusty bread or garlic toast for dipping into the runny yolks.',8,6,NULL),(4,'simple chocolate tart',1,'french',2,'This chocolate tart is great for those chocofreaks who turn up out of the blue, as it is dead quick to make. I think this particular tart cries out for a slightly thicker pastry shell. The better the chocolate you can buy, the tastier it will be.',5,'dark chocolate',NULL,'gourmet eats',16,'Sometimes this mixture looks like it has split. Allow to cool down a bit more and whisk in a little extra cold milk until smooth.','','',20,5,NULL),(5,'greek chicken pasta',0,'greek',2,'On the Greek island of Andros they serve variations of this undeniably delicious pasta – it’s the easiest thing to put together',4,'chicken thighs',NULL,'international flavors',8,'Use high-quality feta cheese for authentic Greek flavor.','Toss the pasta with a splash of lemon juice and zest for brightness.','Garnish with fresh herbs like parsley or oregano for a pop of color and flavor.',60,30,NULL),(6,'bbq chicken',0,'american',4,'American',5,'chicken thighs',NULL,'comforting classics',6,'Marinate the chicken in BBQ sauce for at least 30 minutes to enhance flavor.','Grill the chicken over medium heat to prevent burning and ensure even cooking.','Baste the chicken with additional BBQ sauce while grilling for extra flavor and moisture.',45,15,NULL),(7,'duck carnitas',0,'mexican',3,'Slow-roasting duck legs with just a handful of ingredients transforms them into delicious, melt-in-the-mouth carnitas. You only need 10 minutes of prep, and the oven will do the rest.',5,'duck leg',NULL,'gourmet eats',2,'Slow cook the duck in its own fat for tender and flavorful meat.','Shred the duck meat and crisp it up in a skillet for added texture.','Serve the duck carnitas with warm tortillas and your favorite toppings like salsa and guacamole.',200,10,NULL),(8,'spinach & feta filo pie',0,'greek',3,'This cheesy, flaky pie makes a cracking weekend lunch. Serve with a selection of salads and flatbreads, or simply by itself with a dollop of thick, seasoned yoghurt.',12,'feta cheese',NULL,'comforting classics',5,'Layer the filo pastry sheets with melted butter for a flaky and golden crust.','Squeeze out excess liquid from the cooked spinach to prevent the pie from becoming soggy.','Use a sharp knife to cut the pie into neat portions after baking.',20,10,NULL),(9,'chicken goujons',0,'english',2,'When ingredients work together to maximize their nutritional impact, we like that! Here, the fat in the avocado and oil helps us to absorb fat-soluble vitamin K from the lettuce.',10,'chicken breasts',NULL,'quick & tasty',4,'Marinate the chicken strips in buttermilk or yogurt for tender and juicy meat.','Coat the chicken in seasoned breadcrumbs for extra flavor and crunch.','Fry the chicken goujons in batches to ensure even cooking and crispiness.',18,5,NULL),(10,'epic avo & trout on toast',0,'spanish',2,'This fresh-flavoured open-style sandwich is a thing of beauty – perfect for lunch on a sunny day.',5,'trout fillets',NULL,'gourmet eats',2,'Choose ripe avocados and mash them with a fork for a creamy texture.','Use smoked trout or salmon for a rich and smoky flavor.','Drizzle with a squeeze of lemon juice and sprinkle with flaky sea salt for brightness and seasoning.',6,2,NULL),(11,'fantastic fish skewers',0,'greek',1,'Perfect for getting the whole family to enjoy eating fish, this quick and easy dish is fun, fresh and zingy, and can be easily rustled up on a weeknight when you’re short on time. Pop them on the barbecue for bonus smoky flavour if the weather’s looking good.',7,'white fish fillet',NULL,'flavorful treats',4,'Marinate the fish in a flavorful mixture of herbs, spices, and citrus juice for at least 30 minutes before skewering.','Alternate fish chunks with colorful vegetables like bell peppers, onions, and cherry tomatoes for a visually appealing presentation.','Grill the skewers over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until the fish is cooked through and slightly charred on the edges.',20,2,NULL),(12,'burrata with cherry tomatoes & minty pistachio pesto',0,'italian',1,'A creamy burrata topped with vibrant cherry tomatoes and a flavorful pesto, complemented by the subtle crunch of toasted sourdough and the freshness of micro salad leaves.',5,'cherry tomato',NULL,'gourmet eats',4,'Choose ripe cherry tomatoes for the best flavor and texture.','Serve the burrata at room temperature to allow its creamy center to shine.','Drizzle the pesto over the burrata and tomatoes just before serving to preserve its vibrant color and freshness.',0,15,NULL),(13,'chinese steak & tofu stew',0,'chinese',3,'flavorful dish that combines tender slices of beef steak with silky cubes of tofu, simmered in a rich and aromatic broth',8,'tofu',NULL,'fusion delights',4,'Marinate the steak in a mixture of soy sauce, ginger, and garlic for at least an hour to tenderize and infuse flavor.','Add the tofu towards the end of cooking to prevent it from becoming too soft and mushy.','Garnish with chopped green onions and a sprinkle of sesame seeds for added freshness and texture.',45,15,NULL),(14,'cheese puffs',0,'italian',2,'Cheese Puffs are a delightful combination of cheesy goodness and crispy texture. Perfect for any occasion, these puffs can stand alone or complement a larger menu. With a simple preparation process and make-ahead option, theyre a convenient yet impressive treat. Just pop them in the oven until golden, then enjoy with a chilled drink for a deliciously satisfying snack.',13,'cheddar cheese',NULL,'homemade favorites',8,'Use a combination of your favorite cheeses for a variety of flavors and textures.','Pipe the cheese mixture onto baking sheets using a piping bag or spoon for uniform and attractive shapes.','Bake the cheese puffs until golden brown and puffed up, and serve warm for the best flavor and texture.',20,15,NULL),(15,'cauliflower cheese pizza pie',0,'american',4,'Roast it, fry it, steam it… Or put it on a pizza! Cauliflower never disappoints. For a unique take on this versatile vegetable, whip up this gorgeous, comforting pizza pie.',4,'cheddar cheese',NULL,'comforting classics',4,'Pre-cook the cauliflower crust slightly before adding toppings to ensure a crispy base.','Customize with your favorite pizza toppings such as pepperoni, mushrooms, or olives.','Bake until the cheese is bubbly and golden brown, and let it cool slightly before slicing and serving.',45,25,NULL),(16,'fudge cake',1,'american',2,'Indulge in the decadent delight of this gooey chocolate fudge cake, a treat thats as easy to make as it is to enjoy. Begin by preheating your oven and breaking up the chocolate, combining it with butter, sugar, almonds, cocoa powder, and a pinch of salt in a food processor until smooth. Add eggs and flour to create a velvety batter. Butter a baking dish, coat it with cocoa powder, then pour in the batter. Sprinkle broken fudge over the top and bake until just set with a slight wobble. Serve warm, paired with crème fraîche, vanilla ice cream, or double cream, for a truly indulgent experience.',4,'dark chocolate',NULL,'sweet indulgences',12,'Use high-quality cocoa powder and chocolate for a rich and intense chocolate flavor.','Line the cake pan with parchment paper and grease the sides to ensure easy removal after baking.','Allow the cake to cool completely before frosting to prevent the frosting from melting and sliding off.',20,10,NULL),(17,'chocolate chip cookies',1,'american',1,'You can’t beat a good homemade cookie. These ones are soft, chewy, delicious, and really simple to make',4,'chocolate',NULL,'sweet indulgences',20,'Chill the cookie dough in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes before baking to prevent spreading and ensure thick, chewy cookies.','Use a combination of chocolate chips and chunks for a variety of chocolate textures.','Flatten the cookie dough slightly with the palm of your hand before baking for even cooking and a uniform shape.',20,10,NULL),(18,'singapore-style chilli tofu',0,'singaporean',4,'This recipe was inspired by the stunning dish Singapore-style chilli prawns, which is itself a version of the famous Singapore chilli crab. Tofu can sometimes get a bad rap, but it makes a fantastic alternative to prawns, especially midweek. It has a relatively long shelf-life, so is great to have on hand in the fridge. Frying it until crispy gives it great texture, and it absorbs all the flavours of the sauce – and this dish is ALL about the sauce. It even converted my tofu-fearing husband.',7,'rice',NULL,'international flavors',2,'Press the tofu before marinating to remove excess moisture and improve texture.','Adjust the amount of chili sauce and spices according to your preferred level of heat.','Garnish with sliced green onions and chopped peanuts for extra flavor and texture.',25,25,NULL),(19,'classic ratatouille',0,'english',1,'This moreish Mediterranean-style vegetable stew is perfect for a super-healthy midweek supper.',6,'tomato',NULL,'classic comfort',4,'Use a variety of colorful vegetables such as eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers, and tomatoes for visual appeal.','Cook the vegetables separately before combining to ensure they are cooked evenly and maintain their individual textures.','Garnish with fresh herbs like basil or thyme for a burst of freshness and flavor.',45,30,NULL),(20,'tomato rice',0,'spanish',3,'This makes a great lunch with some fried chorizo on the side, or a side dish with roast chicken or lamb. Most of the time I make it, eat a portion and then use the deliberate leftovers to make the rice cake(s) (on page 54 of Home Food), which are the real bomb. I use brown rice at home as it is more nutritious and flavoursome, but in this recipe method I include a method for using white rice, too. If you decide to use brown rice, I recommend soaking it in advance: it takes two minutes to pour some water over the rice, but then it cooks much more quickly.',5,'rice',NULL,'quick & tasty',3,'Use ripe, juicy tomatoes for the best flavor.','Toast the rice in oil or butter before adding the liquid to enhance its nutty flavor.','Add a pinch of sugar to balance the acidity of the tomatoes and enhance their sweetness.',25,25,NULL),(21,'mushroom stroganoff',0,'french',2,'Mushroom stroganoff is a hearty and flavorful dish featuring tender mushrooms cooked in a creamy sauce. Inspired by the classic beef stroganoff, this vegetarian version swaps the meat for earthy mushrooms, making it a satisfying and comforting option for vegetarians and meat-lovers alike. The mushrooms are typically sautéed with onions, garlic, and herbs, then simmered in a rich and creamy sauce made with sour cream or yogurt. Served over a bed of pasta, rice, or mashed potatoes, mushroom stroganoff is a comforting and versatile dish perfect for any occasion.',6,'mushroom',NULL,'classic comfort',2,'Use a variety of mushrooms for depth of flavor and texture.','Add a splash of white wine or vegetable broth for extra richness in the sauce.','Serve over cooked egg noodles or rice for a complete meal.',10,10,NULL),(22,'mexican style steak',0,'mexican',4,'Here’s a meaty treat inspired by Mexico to get your taste buds fired up – a nice juicy steak served with a fresh, crunchy salsa and an addictively rich satay-style sauce. Ask your butcher to cut you a thick, double steak so you can get it gnarly on the outside and blushing on the inside. You can amplify tenderness and keep it juicy by turning it regularly, trapping the moisture inside while building up a bark-like crust. Peel off the fat and use it to render your potatoes for a deliciously retro side. Get in!',10,'steak',NULL,'international flavors',2,'Allow the steak to come up to room temperature before cooking for more even cooking.','Finely chop all salsa ingredients together for a well-incorporated mixture with balanced flavors.','Blend peanut sauce ingredients until super-smooth, adjusting consistency with water as needed.',23,60,NULL),(23,'apple tart',1,'french',4,'Inspired by the classic French tartelettes you can find in pâtisseries, I’m using shop-bought pastry for convenience. Topped with vanilla ice cream, this is a lovely little number to have up your sleeve.',8,'apple',NULL,'homemade favorites',8,'Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or a dollop of whipped cream for a classic pairing.','Use a sharp knife to thinly slice the apples for even cooking and an attractive presentation.','Sprinkle with a pinch of cinnamon before baking for extra flavor.',20,30,NULL),(24,'mushroom quesadillas',0,'mexican',1,'“Quesadillas are like the pizza of Mexico. You can pretty much make them with anything and they’ll be delicious, so long as they’re hot, crispy and oozing with cheese. These meat-less quesadillas are quick to make and fabulously tasty. It’s amazing what just a sprinkle of chipotle powder brings to the party! If a serious food emergency is leaving you short on time, skip the guacamole and just dunk in sour cream with a squirt of hot sauce.”',4,'mushroom',NULL,'international flavors',2,'Use a variety of mushrooms for a more complex flavor profile.','Cook the quesadillas over medium heat to ensure the cheese melts evenly without burning the tortillas.','Serve with fresh salsa, guacamole, or sour cream on the side for dipping.',10,5,NULL),(25,'satisfying veggie bake',0,'greek',4,'We all need extraordinarily tasty ways to get in the good stuff, and with five of your 5-a-day per portion, this dish makes me very happy.',3,'mushroom',NULL,'comforting classics',8,'Layer the vegetables evenly in the baking dish for even cooking.','Use a mixture of your favorite vegetables for variety and flavor.','Top with breadcrumbs or grated cheese for a crispy topping before baking.',40,40,NULL),(26,'chestnut carbonara',0,'italian',2,'Oh my days, why has it taken me so long to infiltrate one of my favourite pasta dishes with beautiful chestnuts that can be nutty, crumbly and savoury, but sweet and smooth all at the same time.',3,'pasta',NULL,'fusion delights',2,'Toast the chestnuts before adding them to the carbonara for extra flavor.','Reserve some pasta cooking water to adjust the consistency of the sauce if needed.','Garnish with fresh parsley and grated cheese before serving for a finishing touch.',10,5,NULL),(27,'wild boar ragù',0,'italian',5,'Slow-cooked, tender wild boar gives this beautiful pasta an incredible depth of flavour. Inspired by a no-fuss Tuscan restaurant recipe, this is one of the most famous dishes in the whole region. Paired with silky pappardelle, you can’t go wrong.',11,'wild boar',NULL,'international flavors',12,'Allow the ragù to simmer slowly for a few hours to develop deep flavors and tenderize the meat.','Serve over cooked pasta, such as pappardelle or tagliatelle, for a hearty meal.','Garnish with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley for a burst of freshness.',180,35,NULL),(28,'cheddar cheese & chive scones',0,'english',1,'These savoury scones are absolutely delicious – crispy and golden, but also fluffy inside – and you can knock them together really quickly. Serve with soup, salad or as part of a ploughman’s lunch. And once youve given these a try, why not take them in a different direction or give a sweet version a whirl – the possibilities are endless.',12,'cheddar cheese',NULL,'homemade favorites',6,'Handle the dough gently to avoid overworking it, which can result in tough scones.','Brush the tops of the scones with beaten egg or milk before baking for a shiny, golden finish.','Serve warm with butter or your favorite savory spread for a delicious snack or accompaniment to soup.',12,10,NULL),(29,'eggless chocolate cake',1,'american',2,'There’s no need for eggs in this incredible chocolate cake. Crisp on the outside and oozy on the inside, it’s so easy and so delicious. It’ll make you happy for sure!',7,'dark chocolate',NULL,'sweet indulgences',12,'Sift the dry ingredients to ensure a light and fluffy cake texture.','Use room temperature ingredients to ensure proper mixing and a uniform batter.','Cool the cake completely before frosting to prevent the frosting from melting and sliding off.',28,2,NULL),(30,'simple chocolate tart',1,'french',1,'This chocolate tart is great for those chocofreaks who turn up out of the blue, as it is dead quick to make. I think this particular tart cries out for a slightly thicker pastry shell. The better the chocolate you can buy, the tastier it will be.',7,'dark chocolate',NULL,'sweet indulgences',16,'Use high-quality chocolate for the best flavor and texture.','Blind bake the tart crust before adding the chocolate filling to prevent it from becoming soggy.','Garnish with fresh berries or a dusting of cocoa powder before serving for an elegant touch.',30,10,NULL),(31,'apple crumble cookies',1,'french',2,'Fruity, crumbly, buttery joy',6,'apple',NULL,'sweet indulgences',24,'Use firm and tart apples like Granny Smith for the best texture and flavor in the cookies.','Incorporate cinnamon and nutmeg into the cookie dough for warm and cozy flavors.','Top each cookie with a generous sprinkle of crumble topping for added texture and sweetness.',20,4,NULL),(32,'crispy chicken',0,'american',1,'A firm family favourite. Bashing the chicken before you coat it in flavoured crumbs makes it more tender, means it will cook quicker, and is fun for kids to do. Pair this classic with whatever sides you fancy – a simple chopped salad always goes down well.',7,'chicken breasts',NULL,'classic comfort',2,'Marinate the chicken in buttermilk or yogurt for at least 30 minutes to tenderize and flavor the meat.','Use a mixture of flour and breadcrumbs seasoned with your favorite spices for the coating.','Fry the chicken in hot oil until golden brown and crispy, and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.',10,5,NULL),(33,'sausage & squash chilli',0,'spanish',5,'When the evenings start to get darker and the weather gets colder, you can’t beat a good old chilli. This one is a proper family favourite – it’s super simple to make and the kids love it. You can easily double this recipe, so it’s perfect for big get-togethers like Bonfire Night.',6,'sausage',NULL,'hearty dinners',8,'Use a combination of spicy and mild sausages for a balanced flavor profile.','Add diced butternut squash or pumpkin for sweetness and texture in the chili.','Serve the chili with a dollop of sour cream or Greek yogurt and a sprinkle of chopped fresh cilantro for freshness.',60,60,NULL),(34,'stir-fried vegetables',0,'japanese',1,'There are so many things to love about this stir-fry recipe – its quick, tasty and full of goodness',5,'green cabbage',NULL,'quick & tasty',2,'Cut vegetables into uniform sizes for even cooking.','Preheat the wok or pan until hot before adding the vegetables to ensure quick and even cooking.','Stir-fry the vegetables over high heat for a short time to retain their crispness and vibrant colors.',5,10,NULL),(35,'sticky chinese ribs',0,'chinese',4,'Having super-tender fall-off-the-bone pork ribs, shining with a sticky Chinese glaze, always excites me. I remember when I first tried ribs like these – I was about 7 or 8 years old, having a family meal at our local Chinese restaurant, and I remember thinking wow – I’d never tried anything like that before. Bundled with other great dishes like noodles and stir-fried rice, it was beyond exciting. My face and hands were absolutely covered in sauce and that’s how you should be after tucking into these little beauties. Get stuck in',10,'pork',NULL,'flavorful treats',6,'Marinate the ribs overnight in a mixture of soy sauce, honey, garlic, and ginger for maximum flavor.','Bake the ribs in the oven until tender, then brush with additional glaze for a sticky and glossy finish.','Garnish with sliced green onions and sesame seeds before serving for added freshness and texture.',180,30,NULL),(36,'pork, spring green & black bean stir-fry',0,'chinese',2,'Track down a pack of fermented black beans from a Chinese supermarket or online, and a deeply savoury dish can be yours.',5,'pork',NULL,'international flavors',4,'Slice the pork thinly against the grain for tenderness.','Stir-fry the pork over high heat to achieve a crispy exterior while keeping the meat juicy.','Add the spring greens and black beans towards the end of cooking to maintain their vibrant color and crisp texture.',5,30,NULL),(37,'roast duck with marsala gravy',0,'chinese',3,'This crispy roast duck is a fuss-free alternative to the traditional Sunday roast.',11,'duck',NULL,'gourmet eats',6,'Rub the duck with a mixture of salt, pepper, and herbs before roasting for flavor.','Roast the duck on a rack in the oven to allow air to circulate evenly and ensure crispy skin.','Make the Marsala gravy with pan drippings, Marsala wine, and chicken broth for a rich and flavorful sauce.',80,60,NULL),(38,'prawn & crab wontons',0,'chinese',2,'These simple and delicious steamed wontons are the perfect nibbles for feeding a crowd',3,'prawn',NULL,'international flavors',30,'Use fresh, high-quality seafood for the best flavor and texture in the wonton filling.','Seal the wontons tightly to prevent filling from leaking during cooking.','Serve the wontons with a dipping sauce made from soy sauce, rice vinegar, and chili oil for extra flavor.',10,40,NULL),(39,'mochi',1,'japanese',3,'Mochi is one of the most popular sweet treats in Japan, made from mochigome, a sticky variety of rice, and usually filled with ice cream. They are associated with New Year celebrations as they symbolize good luck, health, and prosperity. This recipe features rice flour and milk as a base, and luscious spreads as a filling for the yummiest mochi!',13,'icing sugar',NULL,'traditional delicacies',15,'Use glutinous rice flour for a chewy and stretchy texture.','Add food coloring or flavorings like matcha powder or cocoa powder for variety.','Dust the mochi with cornstarch or potato starch to prevent sticking.',0,30,NULL),(40,'chicken noodle salad',0,'japanese',1,'An original and filling Asian-style salad with noodles, chicken, and vegetables! Prepare this hassle-free recipe in only 15’ and enjoy it as an appetizer or even as a main course!',14,'chicken breasts',NULL,'hearty dinners',5,'Use thin rice noodles or vermicelli for a light and refreshing salad base.','Toss the noodles with a tangy dressing made from lime juice, fish sauce, and sugar for authentic flavor.','Top the salad with grilled or poached chicken for protein and texture.',15,15,NULL),(41,'vegan sushi',0,'japanese',2,'The name says it all!',7,'rice',NULL,'international flavors',12,'Use fresh and colorful vegetables like cucumber, avocado, carrot, and bell pepper for filling.','Experiment with different ingredients such as tofu, marinated mushrooms, or pickled radish for variety.','Roll sushi tightly using a bamboo mat to ensure it holds together well.',10,15,NULL),(42,'fried rice',0,'japanese',2,'classic japanese dish',7,'rice',NULL,'quick & tasty',3,'Use day-old cooked rice for the best texture, as freshly cooked rice can become mushy.','Add vegetables like peas, carrots, and green onions for flavor and color.','Fry the rice in hot oil and toss constantly to prevent sticking and achieve a nice crispy texture.',10,10,NULL),(43,'bao buns',0,'singaporean',3,'the asian sandwich!',9,'flour',NULL,'international flavors',10,'Knead the dough until smooth and elastic for soft and fluffy buns.','Let the dough rise in a warm place until doubled in size before shaping and steaming.','Fill the buns with your favorite savory or sweet fillings, such as braised pork, BBQ chicken, or red bean paste.',30,35,NULL),(44,'spring rolls',0,'singaporean',3,'Finger food with lots of veggies!',10,'wonton wrapper',NULL,'international flavors',10,'Use rice paper wrappers softened in warm water for rolling the spring rolls.','Add a variety of fresh vegetables, herbs, and cooked protein like shrimp or tofu for filling.','Roll the spring rolls tightly and seal the edges with a mixture of water and cornstarch to prevent them from falling apart during frying.',20,20,NULL),(45,'tres leches cake',1,'mexican',2,'Tres Leches Cake is a classic Latin American dessert that translates to \"three milks cake.\" Its a sponge cake soaked in a mixture of three different types of milk: evaporated milk, condensed milk, and heavy cream.',13,'sweetened condensed milk',NULL,'sweet indulgences',10,'Poke holes in the cake with a fork before pouring the milk mixture to ensure it soaks in evenly.','Let the cake chill in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight to allow the milk mixture to fully absorb.','Serve with whipped cream and fresh berries for a deliciously indulgent dessert.',35,10,NULL),(46,'chicken tacos',0,'mexican',2,'Chicken tacos are a popular Mexican-inspired dish featuring tender and seasoned chicken served in soft or crispy tortillas.',8,'chicken thighs',NULL,'international flavors',6,'Marinate the chicken in a flavorful blend of spices and citrus juice for at least 30 minutes before grilling or pan-searing.','Serve the tacos with a variety of toppings such as salsa, guacamole, shredded lettuce, and cheese for customization.','Warm the tortillas before serving to make them more pliable and enhance their flavor.',10,10,NULL),(47,'prawn tacos',0,'mexican',2,'Shrimp tacos are a delicious and flavorful Mexican-inspired dish featuring tender shrimp served in soft or crispy tortillas.',14,'prawn',NULL,'international flavors',6,'Marinate the prawns in a zesty mixture of lime juice, garlic, and chili powder for extra flavor.','Grill or sauté the prawns until they are pink and opaque.','Serve the tacos with fresh toppings like cabbage slaw, avocado slices, and cilantro for a vibrant and tasty meal.',10,10,NULL),(48,'sweet cheese phyllo pie from chana- bougatsa',1,'greek',2,'A traditional Cretan recipe that will have everyone drooling! This “bougatsa” features crispy, buttery phyllo and a creamy filling with sweet Greek cheeses!',23,'granulated sugar',NULL,'traditional delicacies',8,'Use a mixture of cheeses like feta and ricotta for a creamy and tangy filling.','Layer the phyllo sheets with melted butter or olive oil to ensure a crispy and golden crust.','Dust the top with powdered sugar and cinnamon for a sweet and aromatic finish.',20,15,NULL),(49,'spanish tortilla (potato omelet)',0,'spanish',1,'The Spanish tortilla is a classic dish in Spanish cuisine. Its a simple but delicious omelet made with eggs, potatoes, onions, and sometimes other ingredients like peppers or chorizo.',13,'egg',NULL,'traditional delicacies',4,'Slice the potatoes thinly and cook them until they are tender but not browned for the best texture.','Use plenty of beaten eggs to bind the potatoes together and create a fluffy omelet.','Cook the tortilla over low heat and flip it carefully to ensure even cooking and a golden exterior.',20,10,NULL),(50,'baked fish and chips',0,'english',2,'a healthier twist on the classic British dish',23,'cod',NULL,'comforting classics',4,'Use a light and flaky fish like cod or haddock for the best results.','Coat the fish in seasoned breadcrumbs or batter for a crispy and flavorful crust.','Serve with oven-baked potato wedges for a healthier twist on the classic dish.',50,20,NULL),(51,'singapore-style fried rice',0,'singaporean',3,'There are so many variations on this wonderful dish – for me, it’s all about sumptuous fluffy rice with tang and seasoning. Classically there’d be some sort of smoky ribs or ham in the mix, but you can use the principle of this recipe to suit what you’ve got in the fridge and, of course, you can go veggie if you want to. It